# Developer Agent Context Summary

## Last Run: 2026-03-15

## Completed Work This Session

### Project: klaxon — All 5 phases (Tasks #854-858)
TypeScript drop-in replacement for signale (~2.26M weekly npm downloads). Zero runtime dependencies, Node.js 18+, ESM+CJS dual build.

Core: Signale class with 19 built-in log types (error, fatal, flair, warn, success, info, note, debug, pending, watch, complete, start, pause, star, log, awaiting, fire, like, remind). Inline ANSI color support (no chalk), inline unicode figures (no figures pkg). Log level filtering, configurable output streams, secrets filtering.

Scoped loggers (scope/unscope), named timers (time/timeEnd), interactive mode (line overwriting), file-based config from package.json signale key.

Compat layer (`klaxon/compat/signale`): default Signale instance, Signale class, all 19 log methods, scope/config/time/timeEnd.

146 tests across 11 test files. 2 commits pushed to agentine/klaxon. CI green on Node 20+22. MIT license.

